[{"id":"VH964463","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two particles with a charge of positive q, that are placed in three different positions labeled A through C. In position A, the two particles are shown at a distance of d apart. In position B, the two particles are shown at a larger distance, of 2 d, apart. In position C, the two particles are shown at a smaller distance, of one half d, apart.\" height=\"83\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH964463.g01.png\" width=\"485\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical particles, each with a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, are placed near each other. The figure shows three different situations, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, with the particles held at three different distances. In which situation is the magnitude of the electric force exerted by one charge on the other charge the greatest?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH964463_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">None of the situations; the forces between the two particles form a Newtonâ€™s Third Law pair, so the electric force of one charge on the other charge is always the same.</p>"],"answer":2}]